I’ve heard that we should fear the flu more than this coronavirus. Which is incorrect. The average flu kills one in 3000 that are infected. This coronavirus is killing one in fifty. It is very transmissible, you are contagious even before you develop symptoms, and it is doubling every 59 hours. So by March, absent a vaccine there will be more than 3 million infected and sixty thousand dead.

Not that we should panic or anything..... but we should be wary. This one is poised to be big.
